1
00:00:01,667 --> 00:00:02,933
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

2
00:00:03,133 --> 00:00:05,433
<i>Some things have gone
missing from my house.</i>

3
00:00:05,433 --> 00:00:06,700
<i> I took them.</i>

4
00:00:06,700 --> 00:00:07,933
<i> Your burner phone.</i>

5
00:00:09,533 --> 00:00:10,667
[PHONE CHIMES]

6
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:12,133
The photo of you and Uncle Andy.

7
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:16,067
- [YELLING]
- [SLAMMING]

8
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:18,533
<i>He never admitted
what he did to Leon.</i>

9
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:20,767
<i>He also denied
knowing De La Paz.</i>

10
00:00:20,767 --> 00:00:22,833
<i> He confessed,
then tried to clear his name.</i>

11
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:25,033
<i>We need to find
that treasure now.</i>

12
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:27,433
<i> For justice for
our fathers' deaths.</i>

13
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,800
<i> What did the candle say?</i>

14
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:31,400
<i> Where is Monette?</i>

15
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:32,667
- [SCREAMS]
- [THUDS]

16
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> Help!
</i>[BREATHES HEAVILY]

17
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:36,667
<i> Sir, what's going on?</i>

18
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:38,733
<i>- Monette is dead.
- Monette!</i>

19
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:42,467
[WAILING, BAWLING]

20
00:00:42,467 --> 00:00:44,067
<i> That's not Monette!</i>

21
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:46,433
[WAILING CONTINUES]

22
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,967
It's not just one or two people
who've been killed lately!

23
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:51,100
Don't tell me this hasn't
made you think!

24
00:00:51,667 --> 00:00:53,467
We're doing everything we can

25
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:55,700
to find the culprit
or culprits.

26
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:58,500
Like what?! Huh?!
What exactly are you doing?

27
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,733
Our personnel are stationed

28
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:02,567
around the perimeter
of Hotel 88.

29
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:04,733
We've also reported
everything to the Coast Guard.

30
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:07,000
They're monitoring
the area 24/7.

31
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,033
Sir--

32
00:01:08,067 --> 00:01:10,167
Sir Henri, I'm sorry, but...

33
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:14,533
I'm not questioning
your capability.

34
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:17,567
But how many more people
have to die before this is over?

35
00:01:17,967 --> 00:01:23,900
[HACK STEEL SCRAPING]

36
00:01:25,033 --> 00:01:26,633
[LEON] Are you going
to use that on me?

37
00:01:28,067 --> 00:01:29,733
[CHAINS RATTLING]

38
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:30,967
Just kill me!

39
00:01:33,167 --> 00:01:35,667
[HACK STEEL SCRAPPING CONTINUES]

40
00:01:35,667 --> 00:01:37,433
[LEON] Can you hear me, Sandro?!

41
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:40,900
- Just kill me.
- [CHAINS RATTLING]

42
00:01:40,933 --> 00:01:42,833
Come on, please.

43
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:45,633
[HACK STEEL SCRAPPING CONTINUES]

44
00:01:45,633 --> 00:01:46,833
Kill me.

45
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:52,133
[LEON] I said kill me!

46
00:01:52,133 --> 00:01:56,967
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:01:56,967 --> 00:01:59,467
Andy is involved in this!

48
00:02:00,533 --> 00:02:02,167
We can't just accuse
someone, Martin.

49
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:03,400
- [GIO SCOFFS]
- You know that.

50
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:05,867
But no one else could've
done this except him!

51
00:02:05,867 --> 00:02:08,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:11,667
Don't worry, I'll do everything
I can for this case.

53
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,233
My condolences.

54
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:17,100
I'll keep you updated if there's
any new information.

55
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:23,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

56
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:30,267
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:27,933
[RAPHIE SNIFFLES]

58
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,300
Are you okay?

59
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:36,767
[SNIFFLES]

60
00:03:38,667 --> 00:03:42,067
I didn't know she had
photos like these on her phone.

61
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:46,333
[SNIFFLES]

62
00:03:47,967 --> 00:03:50,133
[RAPHIE] She never even
showed them to me.

63
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,300
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

64
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,033
She was so proud of you.

65
00:03:59,067 --> 00:04:03,333
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:04,467
[SNIFFLES]

67
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:06,167
I was the only one
who became a coward.

68
00:04:09,033 --> 00:04:11,167
I was a coward
to my own dream.

69
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:17,867
That's why I couldn't tell her
right away.

70
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:23,400
Or maybe you just didn't know
how to tell her.

71
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:26,933
Because you didn't
want her to think

72
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,367
you wanted to leave her.

73
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:35,367
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:37,300
[WHIMPERS, SNIFFLES]

75
00:04:38,900 --> 00:04:41,867
Ever since our parents died...

76
00:04:43,933 --> 00:04:46,067
...we've been each
other's strength.

77
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,033
Not even in my imagination...

78
00:04:49,733 --> 00:04:50,767
[SOBS]

79
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:52,167
could I have imagined that...

80
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,000
...this would happen.

81
00:04:54,833 --> 00:04:57,000
[CRIES, SOBS]
But it already did.

82
00:04:57,667 --> 00:05:00,033
[SOBS, SNIFFLES]

83
00:05:00,033 --> 00:05:01,867
I lost my source of strength.

84
00:05:02,933 --> 00:05:04,333
Raphie, we're here for you.

85
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:08,033
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

86
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:09,867
We'll never leave your side.

87
00:05:11,033 --> 00:05:13,900
Me, Kiko, Martin...

88
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,033
We will be your strength.

89
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:23,700
[MARTIN] Sari,
remind me tomorrow.

90
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:26,067
We need to process
Monette's death certificate.

91
00:05:26,933 --> 00:05:30,367
Her hotel insurance is part
of her employment benefits.

92
00:05:31,033 --> 00:05:32,767
We need to complete
all the paperwork

93
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:34,667
so Raphie can receive the claim.

94
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,467
It'll be a big help to him.

95
00:05:38,167 --> 00:05:39,833
Ross will handle
the kitchen for now

96
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:42,000
while we look for
a replacement for Monette.

97
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,767
We still have guests
checked in at the hotel.

98
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:46,767
Where's Kiko?

99
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:48,800
The inventory of supplies
still isn't done.

100
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,500
And who's replacing Raphie
while he's on leave?

101
00:05:52,167 --> 00:05:53,800
Can you hear me?

102
00:05:56,433 --> 00:05:58,833
Sir, it's okay.

103
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:00,367
It's okay?

104
00:06:01,033 --> 00:06:03,067
It's okay to be sad.

105
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:04,967
Sad?

106
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,400
What are you talking about,
Sari?

107
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:09,767
Sir, it's okay to cry.

108
00:06:09,767 --> 00:06:11,167
[MARTIN] I'm not crying.

109
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:15,933
[SARI] It's okay
to feel anything.

110
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,000
Monette died.

111
00:06:20,933 --> 00:06:23,967
She was one of the people
closest to your family.

112
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:26,000
- I don't have time to be sad!
- [ENVELOPES CLATTERING]

113
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:29,700
No! I don't want to! I can't!

114
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,000
[SNIFFLES, WHIMPERS]

115
00:06:34,367 --> 00:06:35,933
Thank you. [SNIFFLES]

116
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,400
So all of you...

117
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,367
[SNIFFLES]

118
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:43,000
while there's still time...

119
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:47,000
...don't waste it.

120
00:06:47,367 --> 00:06:48,500
[RAPHIE SNIFFLES]

121
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:51,333
[RAPHIE] Life is too short
not to be happy.

122
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:55,100
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

123
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,867
[CRIES, SNIFFLES]

124
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:02,200
[MARTIN] No! No!

125
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,800
- [MARTIN BREATHES HEAVILY]
- [SARI] Sir...

126
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,500
[SARI SOBS, CRIES]
That's enough.

127
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:08,367
- Sari... Sari... [EXHALES]
- [SARI] That's enough.

128
00:07:08,367 --> 00:07:10,433
- Sari, let go of me.
- [SARI] That's enough.

129
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,233
- Sari.
- [SARI EXHALES]

130
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,233
- Sari...
- [SARI SOBS]

131
00:07:14,867 --> 00:07:16,000
Let go of me.

132
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:18,567
[SARI EXHALES DEEPLY]

133
00:07:18,567 --> 00:07:21,467
- Please...
- That's enough, sir. [SOBS]

134
00:07:22,067 --> 00:07:24,000
[SOBS] Monette...

135
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,167
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:28,233
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

137
00:07:29,967 --> 00:07:32,133
She was a good person.

138
00:07:37,033 --> 00:07:40,067
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

139
00:07:41,033 --> 00:07:42,200
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

140
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,100
She didn't deserve any of this.

141
00:07:48,233 --> 00:07:49,467
[SNIFFLES]

142
00:07:49,467 --> 00:07:56,467
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:07:59,267 --> 00:08:01,567
Monette did nothing wrong.

144
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,033
Why did this happen, Sari?

145
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,233
Why?

146
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:19,167
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

147
00:08:34,167 --> 00:08:41,133
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

148
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:01,000
[MUSIC FADES]

149
00:09:05,567 --> 00:09:06,600
I'm sorry.

150
00:09:07,267 --> 00:09:12,500
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,600
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

152
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:26,400
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

153
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:27,467
Edward.

154
00:09:29,267 --> 00:09:31,300
I heard what happened
to Monette.

155
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:34,100
My condolences.

156
00:09:38,167 --> 00:09:40,533
Monette was such a good person.

157
00:09:42,967 --> 00:09:45,367
She never wronged anyone.
[EXHALES]

158
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,900
[SIGHS]

159
00:09:46,900 --> 00:09:50,400
All she ever did was
take care of us and love us.

160
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,433
I don't understand
how they could do this to her.

161
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,900
Sorry.

162
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:03,000
Listen to me.

163
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:06,167
There's something
you need to know.

164
00:10:06,167 --> 00:10:09,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

165
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:10,967
What is that?

166
00:10:20,733 --> 00:10:27,700
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:30,000
I'm sorry.

168
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,067
Sorry?

169
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:37,100
- [EDWARD SNIFFLES]
- Again?

170
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:42,733
Didn't you also say that
the last time we met?

171
00:10:43,367 --> 00:10:45,767
You say you're sorry,
but I don't know what for.

172
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:48,200
And now, you're saying it again.

173
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,367
What for?

174
00:10:49,367 --> 00:10:51,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

175
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:55,733
I'm sorry because this is
the last time you'll see me.

176
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,700
- [EDWARD SNIFFLES]
- What?

177
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:04,067
But why?

178
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:07,333
Edward... W-Why...

179
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,733
I don't understand.

180
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:10,600
What's the matter?

181
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,367
You all think that my dad is
doing something wrong.

182
00:11:13,367 --> 00:11:16,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,567
Jade, it's not right that
we keep meeting in secret.

184
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:21,433
[JADE BREATHES DEEPLY]

185
00:11:21,433 --> 00:11:23,267
[EDWARD] Kiko is right.

186
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:25,500
As well as your siblings.

187
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,733
This will hurt both of us.

188
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:31,367
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

189
00:11:31,367 --> 00:11:33,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

190
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,767
[EDWARD] So as early as now...

191
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:37,567
Let's stop this before
things get serious.

192
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:40,367
- [JADE WHIMPERS]
- [EDWARD SNIFFLES]

193
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:41,300
Edward, no.

194
00:11:47,767 --> 00:11:49,767
[WHIMPERING]

195
00:11:49,767 --> 00:11:55,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

196
00:11:55,367 --> 00:11:56,733
[WHIMPERING CONTINUES]

197
00:12:02,133 --> 00:12:03,500
Goodbye, Jade.

198
00:12:05,367 --> 00:12:08,333
[EDWARD EXHALES, SNIFFLES]

199
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:10,733
Edward, no...

200
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:13,767
[WHIMPERING]

201
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:15,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

202
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,300
[JADE SNIFFLES]

203
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:23,333
[WHIMPERING CONTINUES]

204
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:26,633
[LIGHTER SCRATCHING]

205
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:28,433
People say that...

206
00:12:29,533 --> 00:12:31,667
when someone dies...

207
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:35,433
they don't just simply leave.

208
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:39,333
They would walk in the dark.

209
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:43,333
- [WATER PLOPS]
- They'd look for light.

210
00:12:43,767 --> 00:12:47,133
[WOOD CREAKING]

211
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:48,100
And...

212
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:51,567
this boat, Monette...

213
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:55,167
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:57,500
It's not just some light
for you to find.

215
00:13:00,400 --> 00:13:02,367
It's a reminder that...

216
00:13:06,767 --> 00:13:09,767
there are plenty of us here
who love you.

217
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:12,367
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:13:12,367 --> 00:13:13,567
[KIKO] If...

219
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:16,333
you're still carrying
any burden or worry...

220
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,600
Just let them all go.

221
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,400
I'll carry it for you instead.

222
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,767
[SNIFFLES] And you...

223
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:26,800
just rest peacefully.

224
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:32,233
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

225
00:13:32,233 --> 00:13:33,600
Look, bro.

226
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,900
[CHESKA] The lantern
looks so small.

227
00:13:37,167 --> 00:13:40,300
But it still shines so brightly.

228
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:46,367
It's just like Monette,
isn't it?

229
00:13:47,233 --> 00:13:48,767
Even on her own,

230
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:52,333
she brought a light that
shone like none other.

231
00:13:52,767 --> 00:13:53,933
[MONETTE] Kiko!

232
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:56,933
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

233
00:13:56,967 --> 00:13:58,933
[KIKO] Monette! Raphie!

234
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,767
[CHESKA]<i> I've only known Monette
</i> for a short time but...

235
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,367
<i>I felt like she was
a real sister to me.</i>

236
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:11,367
[KIKO]<i> Monette has really
</i> been a part of our family.

237
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:18,900
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

238
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,667
We can't just do nothing.

239
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:30,733
We need to get justice
for Monette's death.

240
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,400
I'll help you, bro.

241
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,567
Thank you.

242
00:14:36,567 --> 00:14:43,533
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:14:46,567 --> 00:14:48,933
[GIO]<i> I hope Raphie can
</i> take all of this in.

244
00:14:49,467 --> 00:14:51,833
The police aren't stopping
in their search.

245
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:55,633
Monette's death will
get justice soon.

246
00:14:55,633 --> 00:15:02,600
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

247
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:04,633
Monette's here now.

248
00:15:17,633 --> 00:15:24,600
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:45,667
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

250
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:48,033
[SNIFFLES] Sister...

251
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:50,700
We're all here together.

252
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,400
[BREATHING SHAKILY]
We're going to be okay.

253
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,533
[SNIFFLES]

254
00:15:58,067 --> 00:16:00,033
I will be okay.

255
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:02,400
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

256
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,533
I promise you that, sister.

257
00:16:05,967 --> 00:16:08,800
[MONETTE] I shouldn't have
supported you in your dreams.

258
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,800
[RAPHIE]<i> Don't say that, sister.
</i> You're cheating.

259
00:16:11,667 --> 00:16:14,667
[MONETTE]<i> We're still siblings
</i> even though we're far apart.

260
00:16:14,667 --> 00:16:17,033
<i>I want you to fulfill
your dreams.</i>

261
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:19,000
[RAPHIE] I love you, sister!

262
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,600
[MONETTE] I love you, sis!

263
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:27,533
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,533
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:48,833
Raphie...

266
00:16:49,767 --> 00:16:51,067
How's Raphie?

267
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:55,000
He's devastated, Ma.

268
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,700
He doesn't know
how to live without his sister.

269
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:01,700
[EXHALES, INHALES DEEPLY]

270
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,667
I'm sorry, kids, but...

271
00:17:04,667 --> 00:17:06,233
I can't help

272
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:09,200
but worry more about Leon...

273
00:17:10,933 --> 00:17:12,900
because of all these killings.

274
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:14,100
Mom!

275
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,667
We've talked about this.
Everything will be okay.

276
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:18,200
I'll make sure of that.
Trust me.

277
00:17:18,767 --> 00:17:20,167
And what are you going to do?

278
00:17:20,167 --> 00:17:27,100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

279
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:35,967
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

280
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:42,500
Justin, dear...

281
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,533
[FRIDA] You don't have to be
strong all the time.

282
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:46,867
You're still young.

283
00:17:48,567 --> 00:17:49,600
No, Mom.

284
00:17:53,633 --> 00:17:54,900
I made a promise to Leon.

285
00:17:56,567 --> 00:17:58,533
I will protect our family.

286
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:02,933
[JUSTIN] Especially now that
we don't know where he is.

287
00:18:04,967 --> 00:18:07,167
I have to fulfill that promise.

288
00:18:07,167 --> 00:18:11,733
No, it's okay to be
weak right now.

289
00:18:11,933 --> 00:18:14,967
It's fine as long
as we have each other.

290
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:21,967
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

291
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,100
What if you're right?

292
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,567
What if something bad
happened to Leon?

293
00:18:29,567 --> 00:18:30,600
[SIGHS]

294
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
Let's just hope for the best.

295
00:18:41,567 --> 00:18:42,600
[SNIFFLES]

296
00:18:52,267 --> 00:18:54,633
[HENRI] Lopez,
please file this for me.

297
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:56,133
Sir, someone's here to see you.

298
00:18:59,867 --> 00:19:00,933
Mr. Arellano.

299
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:03,600
How may I help you?

300
00:19:06,033 --> 00:19:07,100
Sir.

301
00:19:07,100 --> 00:19:08,633
[HENRI] What can I do for you?

302
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,700
I'd like to file a report.

303
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,167
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

304
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:21,267
What is it?

305
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:24,700
It's about Dad...

306
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:26,767
- [SIGHS]
- [DOOR CLOSES]

307
00:19:27,933 --> 00:19:29,967
If there's work
that Edward can't do,

308
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,933
send it to me.

309
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:36,733
Yes, he's taking care
of something.

310
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:39,100
Okay.

311
00:19:39,967 --> 00:19:41,000
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

312
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:47,267
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:55,267
[SANDRO] If you don't want me
to make your son pay,

314
00:19:56,633 --> 00:19:58,733
don't try to run.

315
00:20:00,067 --> 00:20:02,200
If you report to the police,

316
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:05,067
your son is going to die.

317
00:20:06,433 --> 00:20:08,067
You took my child
away from me...

318
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:11,000
so I'll take yours in return.

319
00:20:15,333 --> 00:20:17,333
I will say it again,
Mr. Arellano.

320
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,033
You want to report
your own father?

321
00:20:20,967 --> 00:20:22,133
Dad lied.

322
00:20:23,667 --> 00:20:26,767
He said he didn't know
Marina Dela Paz,

323
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:28,200
but that wasn't true.

324
00:20:29,767 --> 00:20:31,200
How can you say that?

325
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,200
I've seen her call Dad's phone.

326
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:36,000
What did she say?

327
00:20:36,033 --> 00:20:38,133
She told him
about Leon's escape.

328
00:20:39,400 --> 00:20:41,900
Marina is working for Dad,
Sir Henri.

329
00:20:43,133 --> 00:20:45,467
So I won't be surprised
if she had a hand

330
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:47,267
in setting up Leon Almazan.

331
00:20:47,267 --> 00:20:54,200
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

332
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,133
Don't you dare hurt Edward!

333
00:20:58,133 --> 00:20:59,933
If you try to hurt him,
you'll see!

334
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:01,000
Why?

335
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,333
What are you going
to do to me?

336
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,300
Do you think I'm scared of you?

337
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:09,900
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

338
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:13,333
[SIREN WAILING DISTANTLY]

339
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:14,933
[BOTH GRUNTS]

340
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:15,967
[ANDY] Help!

341
00:21:15,967 --> 00:21:17,300
[SIREN WAILING CONTINUES]

342
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:18,333
Help!

343
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:20,933
- [SLAMS]
- Help!

344
00:21:20,933 --> 00:21:22,200
Hurry! That guy--

345
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:24,100
You're under arrest

346
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:27,467
for conspiracy, bribery,
and obstruction of justice.

347
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:28,667
What are you talking about?

348
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:30,200
Sandro's over there!
You should arrest him!

349
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:32,067
Why... Why me? Hey!

350
00:21:32,067 --> 00:21:33,400
Ow! [GROANING]

351
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,133
You have the right
to remain silent.

352
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:36,467
Why are you arresting me?
I didn't do anything!

353
00:21:36,467 --> 00:21:38,400
You have the right
to hire a lawyer.

354
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,767
Anything you say can be
used against you in court.

355
00:21:40,767 --> 00:21:42,733
You got the wrong guy!

356
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:45,400
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

357
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:52,367
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

358
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:01,400
[HENRI] We've arrested
Andy Arellano.

359
00:22:01,833 --> 00:22:03,233
Why, Sir Henri?

360
00:22:03,233 --> 00:22:04,733
Was he the one
who killed Monette?

361
00:22:04,733 --> 00:22:06,733
We don't have any evidence
of that, Luna.

362
00:22:06,733 --> 00:22:09,233
But his connection
to Marina dela Paz

363
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:10,667
has been strongly established.

364
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:12,633
And who confirmed that?

365
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:14,600
His own son.

366
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

367
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:17,733
Edward did?

368
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,833
He reported his own father?

369
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,933
I'm here because I need
people willing to file

370
00:22:24,933 --> 00:22:26,633
a case against him.

371
00:22:27,667 --> 00:22:29,733
[JUSTIN]
I'll go to the station, Mom.

372
00:22:29,733 --> 00:22:31,300
I'll call our lawyer on the way.

373
00:22:31,667 --> 00:22:33,200
[FRIDA] Alright, son.

374
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:36,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

375
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:39,367
Why don't we tell them
what his men did to Luna and me

376
00:22:39,367 --> 00:22:40,833
when we were looking
for the map?

377
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:42,800
Those were Andy's men.

378
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,500
He's the only one
who could've ordered that.

379
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:46,167
[MARTIN] Okay.
I'll take note of that.

380
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,533
What about Monette's death?

381
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:51,500
[GIO] Maybe she heard or
discovered something about him

382
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:52,367
that we don't know.

383
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:53,800
That could be
why Andy killed her.

384
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:56,900
That's possible too.

385
00:22:58,333 --> 00:23:00,367
What about Papa's death?

386
00:23:01,267 --> 00:23:03,733
He admitted that he knew
about the treasure.

387
00:23:03,733 --> 00:23:05,300
He was the only one
who could have a motive.

388
00:23:06,567 --> 00:23:09,667
It's a long shot,
but we can include it

389
00:23:09,667 --> 00:23:11,700
so that he goes down for good.

390
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,633
Give me that, Martin.
I'll take care of it.

391
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:18,533
- [KIKO] We'll go with you.
- [GIO] No.

392
00:23:18,933 --> 00:23:21,400
We need to continue searching
for the map.

393
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:24,467
We can't afford to waste
any more time.

394
00:23:24,467 --> 00:23:31,400
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

395
00:23:32,433 --> 00:23:35,000
We'll see if that bastard can
still find a way out of this.

396
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,000
Here.

397
00:23:43,033 --> 00:23:44,467
You have a list too?

398
00:23:47,267 --> 00:23:48,433
A long one.

399
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,833
That bastard isn't getting away
this time.

400
00:23:53,900 --> 00:23:57,333
But is it true that Edward
reported him himself?

401
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:58,467
That's what they said.

402
00:23:58,900 --> 00:24:00,400
Even I was shocked.

403
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:02,867
Who would've thought

404
00:24:03,467 --> 00:24:05,033
there was still an Arellano
with a conscience?

405
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:06,433
[BOTH SCOFF]

406
00:24:06,433 --> 00:24:09,300
Even his own son couldn't
stomach the things he's done.

407
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:13,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

408
00:24:13,067 --> 00:24:14,000
Wait.

409
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:23,433
[ANDY'S LAWYER]
Please step aside.

410
00:24:25,567 --> 00:24:26,867
No.

411
00:24:28,333 --> 00:24:29,900
You're not leaving this station.
Especially not you.

412
00:24:29,933 --> 00:24:31,800
You're going to rot in prison.

413
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,000
[JUSTIN] Sir Henri.

414
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,567
What's happening?
Why is he being released?

415
00:24:35,567 --> 00:24:36,900
He posted bail.

416
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:38,867
Just like that?

417
00:24:39,867 --> 00:24:41,967
The charges against my client
are bailable.

418
00:24:41,967 --> 00:24:43,733
He has money to cover bail.

419
00:24:44,067 --> 00:24:45,967
So I don't see any problem here.

420
00:24:45,967 --> 00:24:47,600
You don't see a problem?!

421
00:24:49,367 --> 00:24:50,767
That devil...

422
00:24:51,933 --> 00:24:53,033
gets to walk free again

423
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:55,433
while the people around us
keep dying one by one!

424
00:24:56,733 --> 00:24:58,633
Look, I heard about
what happened.

425
00:24:58,633 --> 00:25:00,400
And I'm really sorry
for your loss.

426
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:02,400
I knew Monette too---

427
00:25:02,433 --> 00:25:04,800
Don't you dare say
Monette's name.

428
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:07,033
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

429
00:25:07,033 --> 00:25:08,633
You are a murderer.

430
00:25:10,367 --> 00:25:12,767
I didn't kill anyone.

431
00:25:13,733 --> 00:25:14,767
Let's go.

432
00:25:15,467 --> 00:25:16,633
[SIGHS]

433
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:20,967
You may get away
with what you've done today,

434
00:25:20,967 --> 00:25:22,767
but we won't stop
coming after you...

435
00:25:23,433 --> 00:25:24,800
Andy Arellano.

436
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:31,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

437
00:25:34,033 --> 00:25:36,367
<i>This will be the last time
you ever see me.</i>

438
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:38,567
<i>From now on,
just forget I'm alive.</i>

439
00:25:38,567 --> 00:25:40,133
<i>We're in even
more danger now.</i>

440
00:25:40,133 --> 00:25:41,933
<i>We cannot risk
your lives here.</i>

441
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:43,033
<i> You should leave.</i>

442
00:25:43,033 --> 00:25:44,167
<i> Both of you.</i>

443
00:25:44,167 --> 00:25:45,867
<i>Your investigations have
actually led somewhere.</i>

444
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,433
<i>This time, I'm not going
to stop you.</i>

445
00:25:47,433 --> 00:25:48,700
<i> I'm coming with you.</i>

446
00:25:48,700 --> 00:25:50,833
<i>I want justice
for Monette's death.</i>

447
00:25:50,833 --> 00:25:52,867
<i>I've been worried sick
about him,</i>

448
00:25:52,867 --> 00:25:55,033
<i> and then that's what I see?</i>

449
00:25:55,033 --> 00:25:56,900
<i> Jade, I worry about you...</i>

450
00:25:56,900 --> 00:25:58,567
<i> not just as a friend.</i>

451
00:25:58,567 --> 00:26:00,133
<i>I've liked you
for a long time, Jade.</i>

452
00:26:00,133 --> 00:26:01,600
<i> Since we were kids.</i>
